  <span id="freeText15635036941463265890" style="display:none"><i>Briefly</i>: This book paints a dark and chaotic picture of Calcutta in the early 1980s. I wouldn't label it outright "horror," but there are some creepy, disturbing scenes in here. The few main characters are well written and memorable. The story starts off slowly and builds in intrigue and tension as it moves forward. The final third of the book is page-turningly addictive. I was almost racing to the end to find out what happened next. <br /><br />I read Simmons's <i>Hyperion</i> many years ago and loved it. This book has reminded me to read more by Simmons. Do you have any recommendations?<br /><br />Full review can be found here: <a target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow" href="https://biginjapangrayman.wordpress.com/2021/02/21/song-of-kali-1985-by-dan-simmons/">https://biginjapangrayman.wordpress.c...</a></span>
