<div id="review_3842904308" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3842904308" />
    <a title="Dylan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/91403015-dylan"><img alt="Dylan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1610316800p2/91403015.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3842904308?book_show_action=true">Feb 18, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Dylan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Dylan" href="/user/show/91403015-dylan">Dylan</a>
      </span>

          marked it as dnf


          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/36515401-song-of-kali">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/91403015-dylan?shelf=ebook">ebook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/91403015-dylan?shelf=kindle-unlimited">kindle-unlimited</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/91403015-dylan?shelf=horror">horror</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3842904308" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4572523014024434713">DNF @ 25%<br/><br/>Pretty disappointed that my first Simmons read after Hyperion and Fall of Hyperion (two of my favorite books) was such a let down for me. The premise is intriguing but I really disliked the protagonist and none of the side characters thus far were interesting. Also pretty much nothing had happened by this point in the book and I&apos;m not opposed to a slow-burn horror but that only works if you&apos;ve got some kind of tension/underlying creepiness which just wasn&apos;t present. I just found it so d</span>
  <span id="freeText4572523014024434713" style="display:none">DNF @ 25%<br /><br />Pretty disappointed that my first Simmons read after Hyperion and Fall of Hyperion (two of my favorite books) was such a let down for me. The premise is intriguing but I really disliked the protagonist and none of the side characters thus far were interesting. Also pretty much nothing had happened by this point in the book and I'm not opposed to a slow-burn horror but that only works if you've got some kind of tension/underlying creepiness which just wasn't present. I just found it so dull, couldn't be bothered to carry on with it.</span>
